2015-12-01 16:16:29		SPELL_MENU(1)                                                                       User Contributed Perl Documentation                                                                      SPELL_MENU(1)
2015-12-01 16:16:29		NAME
2015-12-01 16:16:29		       spell_menu - popup menu for the weechat spell checker (weechat edition)
2015-12-01 16:16:29		USAGE
2015-12-01 16:16:29		       type the tab key on a misspelt word to bring up the correction pop-up. make sure you have set
2015-12-01 16:16:29		         aspell.check.enabled on
2015-12-01 16:16:29		         aspell.check.suggestions >-1
2015-12-01 16:16:29		       and a dictionary set, e.g in
2015-12-01 16:16:29		         aspell.check.default_dict
2015-12-01 16:16:29		       you also need to have a menu script, if you don't have it yet:
2015-12-01 16:16:29		         /script install menu.pl
2015-12-01 16:16:29		       hint: if it breaks your tab completion, you can toggle the spell checker (default key in weechat is Alt+S)
2015-12-01 16:16:29		CAVEATS
2015-12-01 16:16:29		       Â·   on update of spell_menu from v0.3 to v0.4 you might need to do
2015-12-01 16:16:29		             /unset menu.var.spell.*
2015-12-01 16:16:29		             /script reload spell_menu
2015-12-01 16:16:29		           to get rid of stale entries. sorry about that.
2015-12-01 16:16:29		SETTINGS
2015-12-01 16:16:29		       the settings are usually found in the
2015-12-01 16:16:29		         plugins.var.perl.spell_menu
2015-12-01 16:16:29		       namespace, that is, type
2015-12-01 16:16:29		         /set plugins.var.perl.spell_menu.*
2015-12-01 16:16:29		       to see them and
2015-12-01 16:16:29		         /set plugins.var.perl.spell_menu.SETTINGNAME VALUE
2015-12-01 16:16:29		       to change a setting "SETTINGNAME" to a new value "VALUE". Finally,
2015-12-01 16:16:29		         /unset plugins.var.perl.spell_menu.SETTINGNAME
2015-12-01 16:16:29		       will reset a setting to its default value.
2015-12-01 16:16:29		       the following settings are available:
2015-12-01 16:16:29		   no_complete
2015-12-01 16:16:29		       don't open the spell menu on tab completion. make a binding yourself to call /spell_menu, for example
2015-12-01 16:16:29		         /key bind meta-c /spell_menu
2015-12-01 16:16:29		   complete_near
2015-12-01 16:16:29		       only use tab complete to open the menu if the cursor is next to the wrong word
2015-12-01 16:16:29		   complete_noend
2015-12-01 16:16:29		       don't spell correct with tab if exactly at the end of a word
